# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

LLM-maintained Obsidian-style wiki, scaffolded with [create-llm-wiki](https://github.com/kotiti/create-llm-wiki).

Based on Andrej Karpathy's [LLM Wiki pattern](https://gist.github.com/karpathy/442a6bf555914893e9891c11519de94f) — an LLM maintains a persistent, compounding knowledge base instead of re-deriving from raw documents every time.

## Three layers
- **`{{VAULT_DIR}}/raw/`** — immutable source documents. LLM reads, never writes.
- **`{{VAULT_DIR}}/wiki/`** — LLM-maintained markdown. Read in Obsidian.
- **`CLAUDE.md`** — the schema. Tells Claude Code how to operate on the wiki.

## Getting started
1. Install [Obsidian](https://obsidian.md) and `Open folder as vault` → select `{{VAULT_DIR}}/`. Name it `{{VAULT_NAME}}`.
2. Settings → Community plugins → disable restricted mode → enable `Dataview` and `Marp`.
3. Drop a source into `{{VAULT_DIR}}/raw/sources/`.
4. In Claude Code, run `/ingest {{VAULT_DIR}}/raw/sources/<your-file>`.
5. Browse results in Obsidian's graph view on the side.

## Daily workflow
| Command | What it does |
| --- | --- |
| `/ingest <path>` | Read a source and file it into the wiki |
| `/query <question>` | Ask the wiki; cite and optionally synthesize |
| `/lint` | Health-check: contradictions, orphans, missing cross-refs |

The wiki loads automatically at turn-start (before substantive work) and reflects automatically at turn-end (after substantive work produces domain knowledge). See `CLAUDE.md` and `.claude/rules/wiki-auto-*.md` for details.

## Layout
```
{{PROJECT_NAME}}/
├── CLAUDE.md                   # schema + Claude Code imports
├── {{VAULT_DIR}}/              # Obsidian vault
│   ├── .obsidian/
│   │   └── plugins/{dataview,marp}/
│   ├── raw/
│   │   ├── sources/            # immutable inputs
│   │   └── assets/
│   └── wiki/
│       ├── index.md            # catalog
│       ├── log.md              # changelog
│       ├── entities/
│       ├── concepts/
│       ├── sources/
│       └── synthesis/
├── .claude/
│   ├── agents/wiki-maintainer.md
│   ├── skills/{ingest,query,lint,obsidian-open}/
│   └── rules/
│       ├── wiki-conventions.md
│       ├── wiki-auto-load.md
│       └── wiki-auto-reflect.md
└── {{SCRIPTS_DIR}}/
    ├── obsidian-open.ps1
    └── obsidian-open.sh
```
